006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.adapter;
007
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.metapath.MetapathConstants;
009import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.metapath.item.atomic.IPositiveIntegerItem;
010import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.util.ObjectUtils;
011
012import java.math.BigInteger;
013import java.util.List;
014
015import javax.xml.namespace.QName;
016
017import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
018
019public class PositiveIntegerAdapter
020    extends AbstractIntegerAdapter<IPositiveIntegerItem> {
021  @NonNull
022  private static final List<QName> NAMES = ObjectUtils.notNull(
023      List.of(
024          new QName(MetapathConstants.NS_METAPATH.toASCIIString(), "positive-integer"),
025          // for backwards compatibility with original type name
026          new QName(MetapathConstants.NS_METAPATH.toASCIIString(), "positiveInteger")));
027
028  PositiveIntegerAdapter() {
029    // avoid general construction
030  }
031
032  @Override
033  public List<QName> getNames() {
034    return NAMES;
035  }
036
037  @Override
038  public Class<IPositiveIntegerItem> getItemClass() {
039    return IPositiveIntegerItem.class;
040  }
041
042  @Override
043  public IPositiveIntegerItem newItem(Object value) {
044    BigInteger item = toValue(value);
045    return IPositiveIntegerItem.valueOf(item);
046  }
047}
